r>\n<tr>\n<th align=\"left\"> Grants\n</th>\n<td> nothing\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th align=\"left\"> Time to Wear\n</th>\n<td> 5\n</td></tr></table>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n</div>\n<table style=\"background:#f5faff; border:1px solid #cedff2; width:auto; margin: 0px 5%; margin-bottom:1.25em; font-style:italic; text-align:left; color:#000; padding:1.5em 1em;\">\n\n<tr>\n<td>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width: 100%;\"> A suit made of bands of metal.\n</td></tr></table>\n<p>A <b>banded mail</b> is another intermediate armour.  It is strictly inferior to a <a href=\"/Splint_mail\" title=\"Splint mail\">splint mail</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Tips_and_tricks\">Tips and tricks</span></h2>\n<p>While most intermediate armours are to be generally avoided, this is particularly the case with banded mails - it is strictly worse than a splint mail (same EV penalty but one fewer base AC).  Don't wear it unless you can find nothing better, or you have an absurdly powerful artefact (along the lines of the +8 banded mail of Fun {rF++ rC++ Dam+4})\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span></h2>\n<p>Banded mail was removed from the game in <a href=\"/0.10\" title=\"0.10\">0.10</a>; <a href=\"/Chain_mail\" title=\"Chain mail\">chain mail</a> and other medium armours shifted up a point of AC to take its place.\n</p>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20240916114930\nCache expiry: 86400\nDynamic content: false\n[SMW] In‐text annotation parser time: 0 seconds\nCPU time usage: 0.020 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.019 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 50/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 297/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 1092/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 67/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 3/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   10.995      1 -total\n 78.14%    8.592      1 Template:Armour\n  9.76%    1.073      1 Template:Obsolete\n  9.